  "description": [
    "B4 GUNMAN IS KILLED FLEEING TROOPERS Robert Mahoney 22 Wounds Policeman in Duel Girl Is Held By the Awedted Press LEICESTER Miss August 10A 32yearold gunman Robert Mahoney of Malden Maes was shot fatally yes terday as he fled Into a cellar to escape State troopers A girl companion whose name was given as Helen Oalonek 20 Boston suffered a broken leg earlier as their automobile struck a tree while they were fleeing Mahoney had four gun flghts within three hours State Patrolman George I Doring who first tried to stop the speeding automobile was slightly wounded Doring had recognised the car as one which had figured in an attempted holdup at Stow Mass Fri day night After the accident Mahoney left the Injured girl in the automobile and fled shouting to a farm where milk trucks were loading Leaping in beside a driver the fugitive ordered him to drive toward Worcester At Leicester Mahoney leaped from the truck and ran into yard where he dived into the cellar hole Three bullets struck him He died in a hos pital The girl was held on a charge of being an accessory before the fact of attempted murder The police claimed"
